    "description": "This is a comparative electromagnetic calorimeter geometry evaluation study using Monte Carlo simulation. The task involves designing and simulating three distinct calorimeter topologies (planar sampling, projective tower, and accordion-folded) with identical materials and layer specifications, then systematically measuring their performance characteristics across multiple energy points. The study requires implementing each geometry in a simulation framework, firing electrons at different energies and positions, and collecting detailed energy deposition data to quantify resolution, uniformity, containment, and linearity metrics. This is a multi-geometry detector physics benchmarking task that aims to understand how geometric design choices affect fundamental calorimeter performance parameters.",
